2.20 ⌹[X] - QR Factorization
============================

Z←⌹[X] B computes a QR factorization of the real or complex matrix B.
The axis argument X is used to clear near-0 matrix items to exactly 0.0
during the computation.  Set X←⎕CT if unsure.

   The result Z is a triple (QT R Ri)←Z with the following properties.
Let ⍴B=(M, N).

   * QT is an orthogonal M×M matrix, i.e QT^{-1} = QT^{T}, resp.  QT +.×
⍉QT is the M×M identity matrix I_{M} (with I_{M}←∘.=⍨⍳M).

   * R is an upper triangular M×N matrix, i.e.  R[m;n] = 0 for n < m,
